"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"np.sinc() function returns sin(pi*x)/(pi*x) at the points of the array. When x is 0, the sinc function is mathematically defined to be 1. However, when x is 1, the sinc function is not exactly 0. The sinc function is approximately 0.0 when x is an integer other than 0, but due to floating point precision issues, it may not be exactly 0. Therefore, the assertion sinc_result[1] == 0 may fail.\", \"patch\": \"7,8c7,8\\n< assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n< assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n> np.testing.assert_almost_equal(sinc_result[0], 1)\\n> np.testing.assert_almost_equal(sinc_result[1], 0)\\n\"}"